
Purpose
-------

	To check fault simulation flow for both VC-Z01X (single-user FDB flow) and Z01X in which TRANSIENT FLOP faults are simulated

FLOW
----

	VC-Z01X	: make run_vc_zoix
		>> Compile through VCS 
		>> Fault generation through vc_fcc
		>> Fault report generation through vc_fdb_report
		>> Fault simulation and coverage report generation through vc_fcm

	Z01X	: make run_zoix
		>> Compile through Z01X
		>> Fault generation through fr2fdef
		>> Fault report generation through fault_report
		>> Fault simulation and coverage report generation through fmsh in fdef flow


DIRECTORY STRUCTURE
-------------------
		
		>>	Makefile	:	contains all run commands for both tools
		
		>>	README		: 	guide to demo

		>>	run.f		:	list of source files to be compiled

		>>	user*.dat	:	stimulus files

		>> 	COLLATERAL
			SFF			:	contains SFF files config.sff & faults.sff
			FMSH		:	contains user_local.fmsh 
			FCM 		:	contains fcm_local.tcl

		>>	src			: 	contains source	files
	
LOGS
----

	VC-Z01X
		>> compile 	: 	comp_v.log
		>> vc_fcc 	:	fgen_v.log
		>> toggle	:	fcm.dir/latest/tasks/toggle*/out.log
		>> coats	:	fcm.dir/latest/tasks/coats*/out.log
		>> fsim		:	fcm.dir/latest/tasks/fault*/out.log
		>> coverage	:	fsim_v.rpt

	Z01X
		>> compile 	: 	comp_z.log
		>> fgen 	:	fgen_z.log
		>> toggle	:	__tests__/[test_id]/zoix_rt.log	
		>> coats	:	__fubs__/design/[test_id]/coats.log
		>> fsim		:	__fubs__/design/[test_id]/simout-N0
		>> coverage	:	fsim_z.rpt
		>> fmsh		:	fmsh.log

Notes
-----
	A suitable version of VERDI should be used to run
